<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="518" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/129.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister to Haiti</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>You will visit the Pedernales region, carefully investigate and report
                            fully, bearing in mind the desirability of restoring the status quo at
                            the time of acceptance of the good offices of this Government, which
                            would imply occupation by the Dominican civil authorities of the section
                            east of Pedernales as well as certain points between Lake Fondo and the
                            headwaters.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>